Compare a SSO user to an IAM User:

SSO User: 
	# List SSO instances and get the instance ARN
	aws sso-admin list-instances

	# List permission sets assigned to a specific account
	aws sso-admin list-permission-sets-provisioned-to-account --instance-arn <INSTANCE-ARN> --acount-id <ACCOUNT ID>

	# Get the policies attached to a specific permission set
  	aws sso-admin list-managed-policies-in-permission-set --instance-arn <INSTANCE-ARN> --permission-set-arn <PERMISSION-SET-ARN>
                                                                                                                     
	# Get inline policy for a permission set                                                                           
  	aws sso-admin get-inline-policy-for-permission-set --instance-arn <INSTANCE-ARN> --permission-set-arn <PERMISSION-SET-ARN>

IAM User:     
	# List inline policies
	aws iam list-user-policies --user-name <username>
                                                                                                                     
	# List attached managed policies
	aws iam list-attached-user-policies --user-name <username>                                                         
                                                        
	# List groups the user belongs to (groups also grant permissions)                                                  
	aws iam list-groups-for-user --user-name <username>
                                                                                                                     
	# Get policies attached to each group                                                                              
	aws iam list-attached-group-policies --group-name <groupname>
	aws iam list-group-policies --group-name <groupname>                                                               
                                                                                                                     
  
Get Full Policy Details for Both                                                                                   
                                                                                                                     
	Once you have the policy ARNs, get the actual policy document:                                                     
                                                        
	aws iam get-policy --policy-arn <POLICY-ARN>
	aws iam get-policy-version --policy-arn <POLICY-ARN> --version-id v1   



